history.content: The only way to get into EE courses is to have a seat in all sections (lecture + lab + discussion.)  So if your lab is full, even if you have a seat in discussion and lecture, you won't be enrolled in the class.  The "Switch Sections" feature on Telebears will allow you to adjust the Lab/Discussions sections, without losing your waitlist spot.  However, if you recall in the message, we specifically said that waitlist position will not matter for this class this semester.  Feel free to email me directly and I can look into your situation if you need more help.

I have a section and lab on telebears, but the email that just went out to wait listed students confused me. It said it either are full that I can't get in, and my Lab says its full. There's no chance I'm somehow enrolled in lab but not in lecture right? I don't think any of the other sections I could switch into work with my schedule, and I'm concerned I will lose my waitlist spot if I try to switch sections. What should I do? I am second year EECS.
history.subject: EE16A Confusion
